<li><strong>Premium pricing:</strong> Top ratings = RM 20-40/night more</li>
<li><strong>Less stress:</strong> We handle all review responses</li>
<li><strong>Continuous improvement:</strong> Reviews drive property upgrades</li>
</ul>
<hr class="my-8">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>Q: Should I respond to every negative review?</h3>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Yes. Every negative review deserves a professional response. It shows future guests you care about feedback.</p>
<h3>Q: Can I get a negative review removed?</h3>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Only if it violates Airbnb's review policy (extortion, hate speech, false statements). We can help with removal requests.</p>
<h3>Q: How long does a bad review affect bookings?</h3>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Impact decreases over time. New positive reviews push down negative ones. With active management, impact is 2-4 months.</p>
<h3>Q: Should I offer refunds for bad reviews?</h3>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Only for legitimate service failures. Never offer refunds in exchange for review changes (violates policy).</p>
